\nabla^2 \vec{u}(\vec{x}, t) = \frac{1}{c^2} \frac{\partial^2 \vec{u}(\vec{x}, t)}{\partial t^2}
\vec{u}(\vec{x},0)=\vec{\Phi}(\vec{x})
\left. \frac{\partial\vec{u}(\vec{x},t)}{\partial t}\right|_{t=0}=\vec{\Psi}(\vec{x}) 
